  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bb2 \u0b87\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd    \u0b8e\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bca\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b9a\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel lines again in several places",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "While Power Minister Kanchana Wijesekara had announced on Saturday (27) that fuel queues would be reduced in 2 days, it was observed that people were waiting in long queues to get fuel even today (29) due to shortage of fuel in many parts of the country including Colombo.",
        "Many petrol stations were also closed yesterday due to lack of fuel and banners were hung saying no diesel or no petrol.",
        "Despite the Minister saying that fuel stations are delaying payment of advance payment, the owners of fuel filling stations say that despite pre-manufacturing of fuel, the required volume is not available.",
        "In this situation, the Petroleum Distributors Association has indicated that fuel has been supplied to 60 percent of the fuel stations in the country.",
        "Meanwhile, the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation had announced in a recent statement that fuel is in stock at the Kolannawa and Muthurajawela terminals of the Ceylon Petroleum Storage Terminal.",
        "However, it is to be noted that the distributors are reporting that petrol is not being distributed from the Muthurajawela terminal."
      ],
